column1: The Maclaurin series expansion of $e^{x}$ is

Important Series to remember
\[

f^{\prime \prime}(x)=e^{x} \rightarrow f^{\prime \prime}(0)=e^{0}=1 & f^{\prime \prime \prime}(x)=e^{x} \rightarrow f^{\prime \prime \prime}(0)=e^{0}=1
\end{array}
\]
Applying Maclaurin Series: $f(x)=f(0)+x f^{\prime}(0)+\frac{x^{2}}{2 !} f^{\prime \prime}(0)+\frac{x^{3}}{3 !} f^{\prime \prime \prime}(0)+\ldots$

\]

the cylinder will be inscribed in such a way that its centre passes through the centre of sphere, if $^{\prime} r^{\prime}$ is radius of base of cylinder and 'h' is height, then
\[
\begin{array}{c}
r^{2}=R^{2}-\frac{h^{2}}{2} \rightarrow r=\sqrt{R^{2}-\frac{h^{2}}{4}} \\
V_{c}=\pi r^{2} h=\pi\left(R^{2}-\frac{h^{2}}{4}\right) h \\
\frac{d}{d h} V_{c}=\pi R^{2}-\frac{3}{4} \pi h^{2} \rightarrow h=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{3} R
\end{array}
\]
